1
00:01:26,770 --> 00:01:30,770
=My Dear Guardian=

2
00:01:31,340 --> 00:01:34,120
=Episode 22=

3
00:01:36,410 --> 00:01:38,510
I confessed my feelings.

4
00:01:38,590 --> 00:01:41,330
It's so embarrassing!

5
00:01:58,110 --> 00:01:59,730
Surprise!

6
00:02:04,750 --> 00:02:05,850
Cut it out.

7
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:09,690
Aunt, did you cross over here?

8
00:02:23,410 --> 00:02:25,350
Liang Mu Ze, let's walk around.

9
00:02:25,430 --> 00:02:26,499
Now?

10
00:02:26,579 --> 00:02:27,710
Yes.

11
00:02:27,790 --> 00:02:31,580
Isn't it a shame if we don't walk around
with such a nice dress?

12
00:02:31,660 --> 00:02:33,150
-Aren't you sleepy?
-I'm not sleepy.

13
00:02:33,230 --> 00:02:34,790
Didn't I take a nap just now?

14
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:37,930
I'm feeling great now!

15
00:02:38,630 --> 00:02:39,600
Okay.

16
00:02:44,250 --> 00:02:48,100
♫It feels sweet whenever I think of you♫

17
00:02:48,180 --> 00:02:50,840
♫Even the night breeze revels♫

18
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:55,800
♫The wind blows and the butterflies fly♫

19
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:58,620
♫They are in pairs in the bush♫

20
00:02:59,580 --> 00:03:03,290
♫The night deepens
My longing intensifies♫

21
00:03:03,370 --> 00:03:06,560
♫What do we mean to each other?♫

22
00:03:07,140 --> 00:03:10,880
♫In the four seasons
And to the ends of the Earth♫

23
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:16,300
♫The luckiest thing
Is to have you with me♫

24
00:03:18,710 --> 00:03:22,040
♫The flower in our heart♫

25
00:03:22,650 --> 00:03:25,980
♫Is slowly budding♫

26
00:03:26,470 --> 00:03:31,540
♫Who is secretly speaking kindly to me♫

27
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:37,490
♫My dear you♫

28
00:03:37,990 --> 00:03:39,710
♫Please be brave to dial♫

29
00:03:39,790 --> 00:03:41,490
Let go! Let go!

30
00:03:42,020 --> 00:03:45,470
♫This familiar string of numbers♫

31
00:03:45,550 --> 00:03:47,290
No, I'm running out of energy!

32
00:03:54,870 --> 00:03:55,870
-Here.
-Bring it on.

33
00:03:55,950 --> 00:03:57,820
Three, two...

34
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:00,900
Mother, why can't it fly?

35
00:04:01,350 --> 00:04:03,450
I don't know. Perhaps we did it wrongly.

36
00:04:04,990 --> 00:04:06,210
You messed up!

37
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:10,890
Dr Zhang.

38
00:04:13,110 --> 00:04:14,450
Why are you here?

39
00:04:15,110 --> 00:04:16,890
Perhaps it's destiny.

40
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,870
We meet again.

41
00:04:23,540 --> 00:04:25,470
-Come!
-Don't touch my kite!

42
00:04:25,550 --> 00:04:27,510
There's a problem with your kite.

43
00:04:27,590 --> 00:04:28,870
How do you know that?

44
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:30,990
I'm a doctor. Of course I know.

45
00:04:31,070 --> 00:04:32,170
Let me fix it for you.

46
00:04:37,270 --> 00:04:38,590
Okay, you guys fix it.

47
00:04:38,670 --> 00:04:40,370
I'll go get you some water.

48
00:04:41,170 --> 00:04:42,120
Here, take this.

49
00:04:43,070 --> 00:04:44,450
Let me take a look.

50
00:04:48,150 --> 00:04:49,390
Can you do it?

51
00:04:49,470 --> 00:04:50,570
Rest assured.

52
00:04:51,340 --> 00:04:52,920
You were a tadpole...

53
00:04:53,630 --> 00:04:55,210
when I played the kite.

54
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:58,220
A tadpole?

55
00:04:58,910 --> 00:05:00,250
A frog's baby.

56
00:05:05,750 --> 00:05:07,000
I know what the problem is.

57
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:10,460
Why am I a frog's baby?

58
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:13,010
You're not the baby of a frog.

59
00:05:15,790 --> 00:05:17,650
I'll tell you later.

60
00:05:20,470 --> 00:05:21,690
Drink your medicine.

61
00:05:23,020 --> 00:05:24,040
I don't want to drink it.

62
00:05:25,790 --> 00:05:27,730
The kite has to be fixed
when it has a problem.

63
00:05:28,390 --> 00:05:30,490
People should take medicine
when they are sick.

64
00:05:33,710 --> 00:05:37,110
Can you guarantee that my kite will fly
after I drink the medicine?

65
00:05:37,190 --> 00:05:38,130
Of course.

66
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,850
It's not only the kite,

67
00:05:41,290 --> 00:05:44,830
you might also fly
if you finish the medicine.

68
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:46,550
Okay.

69
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:47,950
Keep your words.

70
00:05:48,030 --> 00:05:49,050
You have my words.

71
00:05:50,460 --> 00:05:51,770
Slow down, don't choke yourself.

72
00:05:56,030 --> 00:05:57,310
-It's not bitter, right?
-It's not bitter.

73
00:05:57,390 --> 00:05:58,930
Okay, give it a try.

74
00:05:59,630 --> 00:06:00,530
Okay.

75
00:06:01,270 --> 00:06:02,870
-Pull it longer.
-Enough.

76
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:04,030
Enough.

77
00:06:04,110 --> 00:06:05,550
-Ready!
-Okay, then.

78
00:06:05,630 --> 00:06:07,830
Here. Ready, go!

79
00:06:07,910 --> 00:06:08,810
Run!

80
00:06:12,510 --> 00:06:13,730
It's flying!

81
00:06:15,440 --> 00:06:16,410
Run!

82
00:06:16,490 --> 00:06:18,460
-Run and it will...
-Feed the line!

83
00:06:18,540 --> 00:06:19,640
Feed the line!

84
00:06:27,730 --> 00:06:28,880
I can't ride anymore.

85
00:06:31,460 --> 00:06:34,110
I shouldn't have listened to you
to come here by bicycle.

86
00:06:34,190 --> 00:06:36,130
We should've been here by now
if we came by car.

87
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:38,740
Are you in a hurry?

88
00:06:38,820 --> 00:06:40,150
I'm exhausted.

89
00:06:41,380 --> 00:06:44,130
How can you operate
when you have such poor stamina?

90
00:06:44,650 --> 00:06:47,010
I'm here to enjoy the cosy sunshine.

91
00:06:47,090 --> 00:06:48,620
I'm not here to train with you.

92
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:51,510
Can't you let me relax
as it's hard to have a rest day?

93
00:06:51,590 --> 00:06:53,910
Then just go home,
and lie down on the sofa to read.

94
00:06:53,990 --> 00:06:54,870
It's very pleasant.

95
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:01,870
So...

96
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:03,830
are you jealous?

97
00:07:03,910 --> 00:07:05,030
I'm not.

98
00:07:05,110 --> 00:07:06,190
You are.

99
00:07:06,270 --> 00:07:07,180
You're jealous.

100
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:08,360
I'm not.

101
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:13,530
You can't lie to me, Liang Mu Ze.

102
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:30,170
You drank my water.

103
00:07:30,750 --> 00:07:31,700
Yes.

104
00:07:31,780 --> 00:07:32,630
What do you mean yes?

105
00:07:32,710 --> 00:07:34,460
Which question are you answering?

106
00:07:34,540 --> 00:07:36,240
Your water, I'm giving it back to you.

107
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:39,150
Are you sure?

108
00:07:39,230 --> 00:07:40,330
I'm sure.

109
00:07:50,670 --> 00:07:51,740
What are you doing?

110
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:52,770
Disinfecting it!

111
00:08:01,990 --> 00:08:03,550
Zhang Yi Chi, you're so amazing!

112
00:08:03,630 --> 00:08:04,890
You can fix everything.

113
00:08:05,390 --> 00:08:07,150
Didn't I tell you?

114
00:08:07,230 --> 00:08:09,250
I'm an old player in kite-flying.

115
00:08:10,880 --> 00:08:13,170
Can you fly kites with me in the future?

116
00:08:14,490 --> 00:08:16,880
Can you fly kites with me in the future?

117
00:08:18,450 --> 00:08:19,630
As long as you're willing to.

118
00:08:33,830 --> 00:08:34,710
Xiao Jun,

119
00:08:36,990 --> 00:08:39,800
the question you asked me last time...

120
00:08:41,470 --> 00:08:44,050
about marrying your mother.

121
00:08:45,670 --> 00:08:47,170
To be honest,

122
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:49,290
I hope that...

123
00:08:49,910 --> 00:08:51,290
I could be this fortunate.

124
00:08:52,430 --> 00:08:53,610
I know...

125
00:08:54,650 --> 00:08:57,270
luck is for those who are prepared.

126
00:08:58,210 --> 00:08:59,470
So I plan to...

127
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:02,170
show my utmost sincerity...

128
00:09:02,870 --> 00:09:05,210
and get along with her...

129
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:10,880
in ways that she prefers
and is comfortable with.

130
00:09:13,310 --> 00:09:14,730
As for the result,

131
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:16,870
I have no idea too.

132
00:09:16,950 --> 00:09:20,010
Even if you ask your mother this question,

133
00:09:20,090 --> 00:09:21,630
she wouldn't know the answer either.

134
00:09:25,530 --> 00:09:28,170
Give us some time, okay?

135
00:09:31,310 --> 00:09:32,850
What if I say no?

136
00:09:33,410 --> 00:09:34,390
If you say no,

137
00:09:36,110 --> 00:09:37,650
I'll tear this string apart.

138
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:39,590
Don't.

139
00:09:39,670 --> 00:09:40,910
Don't do it.

140
00:09:40,990 --> 00:09:42,000
I'm just kidding.

141
00:09:46,230 --> 00:09:49,440
Just come to me if you have any problem.

142
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:51,420
Okay.

143
00:09:53,470 --> 00:09:54,470
Take it.

144
00:09:54,550 --> 00:09:56,450
Pull it tight.

145
00:09:57,070 --> 00:09:57,970
Okay.

146
00:09:59,230 --> 00:10:00,110
Pull it tight.

147
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:01,700
It's tight.

148
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:08,530
-Take a rest.
-Okay.

149
00:10:11,870 --> 00:10:13,250
What are you writing?

150
00:10:14,470 --> 00:10:15,810
A film script.

151
00:10:17,230 --> 00:10:18,290
A script?

152
00:10:19,230 --> 00:10:20,610
It's a job recommended by my friend.

153
00:10:20,690 --> 00:10:22,990
It's a story about the comeback
of a single mother...

154
00:10:23,070 --> 00:10:25,130
as a wedding gown designer.

155
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,460
Comrade Chen Meng Zhen,

156
00:10:32,070 --> 00:10:34,770
how many secrets do you have
that I'm unaware of?

157
00:10:35,310 --> 00:10:36,770
Dr Zhang, thank you.

158
00:10:36,850 --> 00:10:38,030
Thanks for coming to play with Xiao Jun.

159
00:10:38,110 --> 00:10:39,890
I can free up some time to write this.

160
00:10:43,020 --> 00:10:44,810
I'm not here just to accompany Xiao Jun.

161
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:49,250
It doesn't matter,
as long as you're attentive.

162
00:10:53,430 --> 00:10:54,610
It must be tough...

163
00:10:55,350 --> 00:10:57,130
to take care...

164
00:10:58,100 --> 00:10:59,290
of a kid alone, right?

165
00:11:02,110 --> 00:11:04,510
It was a bit hectic at first.

166
00:11:04,590 --> 00:11:06,170
I got used to it as time went by.

167
00:11:07,950 --> 00:11:10,690
Actually, sometimes,
it's not that Xiao Jun needs me,

168
00:11:11,370 --> 00:11:12,690
but it's I who need him instead.

169
00:11:14,390 --> 00:11:18,840
It's Xiao Jun who makes me
have a deeper bond with this world.

170
00:11:21,190 --> 00:11:22,150
When I wake up,

171
00:11:22,230 --> 00:11:24,750
I'll find myself being fearless.

172
00:11:24,830 --> 00:11:28,210
I didn't expect that it was my child
who'd teach me to be brave.

173
00:11:28,650 --> 00:11:29,650
Isn't that incredible?

174
00:11:32,350 --> 00:11:34,270
Sometimes, Xiao Jun and I
don't seem like a mother and a son.

175
00:11:34,350 --> 00:11:35,360
We're more like friends.

176
00:11:37,980 --> 00:11:39,380
For me,

177
00:11:39,460 --> 00:11:42,700
he is a great child.

178
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:45,250
I hope that I am...

179
00:11:45,890 --> 00:11:47,670
a good mother to him too.

180
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:52,240
You've done great...

181
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,270
as a first-time mother.

182
00:11:58,460 --> 00:11:59,770
I think so too.

183
00:12:05,150 --> 00:12:06,020
Eat it.

184
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,050
Take it.

185
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:12,010
The kite got loose!

186
00:12:12,090 --> 00:12:13,110
Hurry, get it!

187
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:26,060
Just take a rest if you're tired.

188
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:34,670
Seems like it's easier to cheer a woman up
by provoking her...

189
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:36,090
rather than encouraging her.

190
00:12:38,030 --> 00:12:39,470
What do you mean?

191
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:40,430
Be careful!

192
00:13:10,570 --> 00:13:11,730
Are you all right?

193
00:13:11,810 --> 00:13:12,870
Liang Mu Ze?

194
00:13:13,740 --> 00:13:14,800
Xiao Jun?

195
00:13:18,430 --> 00:13:19,620
Mr Zhang?

196
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:22,590
You guys...

197
00:13:22,670 --> 00:13:23,770
What a coincidence!

198
00:13:24,180 --> 00:13:25,310
Is this an encounter?

199
00:13:26,470 --> 00:13:28,230
He said it was destiny that sent him here.

200
00:13:28,310 --> 00:13:31,450
And he said I'm the son of a frog.

201
00:13:33,210 --> 00:13:34,450
I...

202
00:13:34,530 --> 00:13:37,710
I'm here to fix this kite.

203
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:39,450
Look.

204
00:13:41,030 --> 00:13:42,730
Dr Zhang is quite idle.

205
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:50,480
Captain Liang, you're quite idle too.

206
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:52,270
Mother, I want to drink water.

207
00:13:52,350 --> 00:13:53,700
Okay, I'll take you there.

208
00:13:53,780 --> 00:13:54,750
Dr Xia.

209
00:13:54,830 --> 00:13:56,240
Dr Xia, what do you want to drink?

210
00:13:56,750 --> 00:13:58,280
Mineral water will do, thank you.

211
00:13:58,360 --> 00:13:59,240
Okay.

212
00:14:01,430 --> 00:14:03,250
Didn't you have one already?

213
00:14:04,330 --> 00:14:05,780
It's poisoned.

214
00:14:08,580 --> 00:14:09,770
What do you two want to drink?

215
00:14:09,850 --> 00:14:11,310
-I'll go with you.
-I'll go with you.

216
00:14:14,830 --> 00:14:15,740
What?

217
00:14:16,550 --> 00:14:18,910
You just ride the bicycle with me.

218
00:14:18,990 --> 00:14:22,600
-I'll go buy the water.
-Just let Mr Zhang go with Ms Meng Zhen.

219
00:14:22,680 --> 00:14:23,610
Right.

220
00:14:24,230 --> 00:14:25,430
I'll go with you.

221
00:14:25,510 --> 00:14:26,390
Okay.

222
00:14:28,830 --> 00:14:29,730
I'm reliable.

223
00:14:30,630 --> 00:14:32,030
-Let's go!
-Xiao Jun, let's go.

224
00:14:32,110 --> 00:14:33,000
Let's go!

225
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,230
Let's go!

226
00:14:56,060 --> 00:14:58,290
Xia Chu, don't be this childish, okay?

227
00:14:58,370 --> 00:14:59,600
What do you mean by that?

228
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:01,070
Is it childish to blow bubbles?

229
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:02,770
I like it, it's none of your concern.

230
00:15:04,020 --> 00:15:05,960
I'm talking about Zhang Yi Chi
and Meng Zhen.

231
00:15:06,040 --> 00:15:07,140
You stay out of it.

232
00:15:14,110 --> 00:15:16,170
It's not your concern too.

233
00:15:18,620 --> 00:15:20,300
I know Zhang Yi Chi.

234
00:15:20,380 --> 00:15:22,410
His love life is too complicated.

235
00:15:24,260 --> 00:15:26,840
He doesn't want to get married
just because he has to.

236
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:28,840
He wishes to find his true love.

237
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:29,930
Is that wrong?

238
00:15:31,250 --> 00:15:32,380
Right, it's not wrong.

239
00:15:32,460 --> 00:15:34,960
But Meng Zhen can't be the cost
of his trial-and-error.

240
00:15:36,660 --> 00:15:39,800
If you don't try it out,
how will you know if it's right or wrong?

241
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:44,560
For some men,

242
00:15:45,270 --> 00:15:47,200
it's enough to be friends with them.

243
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:49,500
It's too dangerous to be lovers with them.

244
00:15:50,550 --> 00:15:52,850
Nothing is more dangerous
than being a special forces soldier.

245
00:15:55,090 --> 00:15:56,940
If it's wrong to be dangerous,

246
00:15:57,470 --> 00:15:59,100
then what does the love
between Ms Meng Zhen...

247
00:15:59,180 --> 00:16:00,080
and your comrade mean?

248
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:02,090
Was it wrong?

249
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:05,000
And...

250
00:16:05,630 --> 00:16:06,930
Liang Mu Ze,

251
00:16:07,470 --> 00:16:09,170
as you're a special forces soldier,

252
00:16:09,910 --> 00:16:11,590
what kind of man are you?

253
00:16:11,670 --> 00:16:13,310
I'm talking about Zhang Yi Chi.

254
00:16:13,390 --> 00:16:14,590
Don't turn this on me.

255
00:16:14,670 --> 00:16:16,630
Obviously, you're too subjective.

256
00:16:16,710 --> 00:16:18,110
No matter if he is Zhuo Ran
or Zhang Yi Chi,

257
00:16:18,190 --> 00:16:20,450
you're biased
against my mentor and friend.

258
00:16:22,140 --> 00:16:23,610
I'll tell you what.

259
00:16:24,990 --> 00:16:26,950
Zhang Yi Chi is my friend too.

260
00:16:27,030 --> 00:16:29,270
Don't compare him to Zhuo Ran, get it?

261
00:16:29,350 --> 00:16:31,150
You don't have the right
to make the decision for your friend.

262
00:16:31,230 --> 00:16:32,790
I didn't make decisions for him.

263
00:16:32,870 --> 00:16:34,350
I just dissuade him in good faith, okay?

264
00:16:34,430 --> 00:16:35,790
They are not suitable, understand?

265
00:16:35,870 --> 00:16:38,390
Being suitable
may give us a right relationship,

266
00:16:38,470 --> 00:16:40,190
but it will never explain
how love happens.

267
00:16:40,270 --> 00:16:42,510
Being suitable means nothing to love!

268
00:16:42,590 --> 00:16:43,770
The water is here.

269
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:17,910
Get off.

270
00:17:17,990 --> 00:17:18,970
We're here.

271
00:17:20,150 --> 00:17:22,989
Slow down.
(Passer-by Bookstore)

272
00:17:23,069 --> 00:17:24,150
Wash your hands first.

273
00:17:24,230 --> 00:17:25,170
Okay.

274
00:17:26,340 --> 00:17:27,960
He has been smiling all day long.

275
00:17:28,780 --> 00:17:29,940
You've worked hard today.

276
00:17:30,020 --> 00:17:31,350
No, I'm happy too.

277
00:17:31,430 --> 00:17:32,850
